      "content": "# Poster Concepts: The Favourite\n\n## About This Document\nThese are key-art directions for a campaign designer. Each concept should read at thumbnail size and stay attached to specific script evidence.\n\n---\n\n## Category: Character-Driven\n\n**Concept 1: ABIGAIL at Court**\n- **Style:** Court portrait one-sheet\n- **Composition:** ABIGAIL framed inside anne's apartments, with costume, posture, and eye line carrying status.\n- **Color Palette:** #C49A47 (Candle Gold), #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue)\n- **Typography:** Tall, restrained serif title with wide-set sans-serif credits.\n- **Tagline:** \"Every favor has teeth.\"\n- **Mood:** Elegant, cruel, watchful\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers drawn to performance, costume, status games, and black comedy.\n- **AI Prompt:** Period black-comedy poster for The Favourite, ABIGAIL in anne's apartments, courtly posture, precise costume detail, sharp wit, no invented characters.\n\n**Concept 2: The Court Watches**\n- **Style:** Formal status tableau\n- **Composition:** ABIGAIL, SARAH, ANNE, HARLEY arranged by rank, intimacy, and suspicion rather than equal heroic scale.\n- **Color Palette:** #C49A47 (Candle Gold), #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue), #171513 (Ink Black)\n- **Typography:** Architectural, quiet, and ceremonial.\n- **Tagline:** \"The room always takes a side.\"\n- **Mood:** Ceremonial, vicious, comic\n- **Campaign Read:** period drama, black comedy, and performance-led arthouse audiences\n- **AI Prompt:** Ensemble key art for The Favourite, ABIGAIL, SARAH, ANNE, HARLEY arranged by court status in anne's apartments, dark comedy, period texture, no unrelated genre details.\n\n## Category: Symbolic / Metaphorical\n\n**Concept 3: The Favor Object**\n- **Style:** Symbolic court-object poster\n- **Composition:** 17 white rabbits isolated like a small instrument of leverage, surrounded by court texture and negative space.\n- **Color Palette:** #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue)\n- **Typography:** Small title, lots of negative space, no decorative texture unless tied to the object.\n- **Tagline:** \"A little thing can ruin a life.\"\n- **Mood:** Precise, poisonous, funny\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who respond to iconic props and period design.\n- **AI Prompt:** Minimal period poster for The Favourite, 17 white rabbits as a court object with social consequence, candlelit restraint, no unrelated props.\n\n**Concept 4: The Room as Court**\n- **Style:** Environmental metaphor poster\n- **Composition:** Anne's Apartments becomes the campaign image, with rank, furniture, animal/prop detail, and a small human figure showing the social order.\n- **Color Palette:** #C49A47 (Candle Gold), #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue), #171513 (Ink Black)\n- **Typography:** Title embedded low in the environment so scale reads first.\n- **Tagline:** \"The court always watches.\"\n- **Mood:** Opulent, tense, decaying\n- **Campaign Read:** period drama, black comedy, and performance-led arthouse audiences\n- **AI Prompt:** Environmental one-sheet for The Favourite, anne's apartments becomes the campaign image, with rank, furniture, animal/prop detail, and a small human figure showing the social order. Graphic readability at thumbnail size, no invented geography.\n\n## Category: Scene-Based\n\n**Concept 5: Scene 12 Signal**\n- **Style:** Scene-led campaign image\n- **Composition:** Politicians race ducks in a makeshift ring.\n- **Color Palette:** #C49A47 (Candle Gold), #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson)\n- **Typography:** Title clear at thumbnail size, secondary copy minimal.\n- **Tagline:** \"Every room has a favorite.\"\n- **Mood:** Conflict\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who want one memorable scripted moment as the campaign hook.\n- **AI Prompt:** Key art for The Favourite, Scene 12: Politicians race ducks in a makeshift ring. Keep only characters and objects named in the script data, no extra plot details.\n\n**Concept 6: Scene 21 Signal**\n- **Style:** Scene-led campaign image\n- **Composition:** Abigail lays raw beef slices on Anne's gout-inflamed legs.\n- **Color Palette:** #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue)\n- **Typography:** Title clear at thumbnail size, secondary copy minimal.\n- **Tagline:** \"Loyalty changes costume.\"\n- **Mood:** Tenderness\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who want one memorable scripted moment as the campaign hook.\n- **AI Prompt:** Key art for The Favourite, Scene 21: Abigail lays raw beef slices on Anne's gout-inflamed legs. Keep only characters and objects named in the script data, no extra plot details.\n\n**Concept 7: Scene 9 Signal**\n- **Style:** Scene-led campaign image\n- **Composition:** Abigail, covered in mud, curtseys before the immaculate Sarah.\n- **Color Palette:** #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue), #171513 (Ink Black)\n- **Typography:** Title clear at thumbnail size, secondary copy minimal.\n- **Tagline:** \"Grace can become exile.\"\n- **Mood:** Judgment\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who want one memorable scripted moment as the campaign hook.\n- **AI Prompt:** Key art for The Favourite, Scene 9: Abigail, covered in mud, curtseys before the immaculate Sarah. Keep only characters and objects named in the script data, no extra plot details.\n\n## Category: Minimalist / Typographic\n\n**Concept 8: The Title as Terrain**\n- **Style:** Typographic conceptual poster\n- **Composition:** The title treated like a court appointment, formal and sharp, with a small prop or animal detail interrupting the symmetry.\n- **Color Palette:** #C49A47 (Candle Gold), #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson)\n- **Typography:** Massive serif or chiseled sans-serif, quiet spacing, no distressed effects.\n- **Tagline:** \"Grace can become exile.\"\n- **Mood:** Iconic, austere, memorable\n- **Campaign Read:** period drama, black comedy, and performance-led arthouse audiences.\n- **AI Prompt:** Minimal typographic poster for The Favourite, formal period title treatment, court texture, one prop or animal detail from the JSON, no unrelated genre language.\n\n**Concept 9: The Production Map**\n- **Style:** Production-design one-sheet\n- **Composition:** A restrained map of anne's apartments, sarah's quarters, kitchen, palace grounds, with one object or event marker per location.\n- **Color Palette:** #C49A47 (Candle Gold), #E6DDC9 (Powdered Ivory), #8B1E2D (Velvet Crimson), #536B85 (Gout Blue), #171513 (Ink Black)\n- **Typography:** Information-design clarity with cinematic restraint.\n- **Tagline:** \"Every room has a favorite.\"\n- **Mood:** Designed, strategic, expansive\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers interested in production design and story structure.\n- **AI Prompt:** Elegant production-map poster for The Favourite, restrained map of the script's major locations with small object or event markers from the JSON, no invented geography.",
